WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:04.560
Back when we were looking for furniture, we&nbsp;
didn't want to spend a whole lot of money,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:04.560 --> 00:00:10.720
but we still wanted our home to at least look put&nbsp;
together. What we ended up doing was we basically&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:10.720 --> 00:00:16.240
sourced all of our stuff from two places. Two&nbsp;
widely available brands, everyone's favorite&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:16.240 --> 00:00:23.040
Swedish furniture store, Ikea, and Japanese&nbsp;
label Muji. So, how did everything hold up after&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:29.440
8 years? Did they live up to our expectations? Is&nbsp;
there anything we regret buying? Let's find out.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:30.640 --> 00:00:35.520
Entering our front door, we are greeted by&nbsp;
these bar chairs, which might be the only&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:35.520 --> 00:00:41.200
normal chairs in our home today. This is where&nbsp;
we have breakfast, where we have our tea breaks,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:41.200 --> 00:00:46.560
and sometimes they are a lifesaver when we are&nbsp;
sick and don't have the energy to sit upright&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:46.560 --> 00:00:52.080
without support. They can be folded and stowed&nbsp;
away to save space, but we have never actually&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:52.080 --> 00:00:58.160
utilized that. They get a bit creaky over time,&nbsp;
so it helps to retighten the screws every once&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:58.160 --> 00:01:04.080
in a while. Overall, they're perfectly fine, they&nbsp;
serve their purpose, and we wouldn't mind getting&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:11.520
these again. The next item are these step stools,&nbsp;
which we've gotten a lot of questions about over&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:18.480
the years. These are possibly our most versatile,&nbsp;
and most frequently used pieces of furniture.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:24.400
They can be used as they're designed, as a stool or&nbsp;
a step ladder, and we've also used them as a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:31.280
makeshift floor desk, a makeshift kneeling stool,&nbsp;
or as workout equipment. They are stackable,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:31.280 --> 00:01:37.440
easy to move around, and we like its clean,&nbsp;
minimal look. But here's the sad part. They&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:37.440 --> 00:01:43.040
have been discontinued, so they're not going to&nbsp;
be easy to find. 10 out of 10, we would definitely&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:48.560
buy these again. In fact, if we knew they would&nbsp;
be discontinued, we might as well have gotten a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:48.560 --> 00:01:55.280
couple more because they are so useful around the&nbsp;
house without taking up much space. Next are these&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:55.280 --> 00:02:02.080
comfortable bean bags. We lounge in these. We take&nbsp;
naps in these. They have these microbeads which&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:07.760
make them feel soft and fluffy, and supposedly,&nbsp;
they don't lose their volume as quickly compared&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:07.760 --> 00:02:14.000
to regular bean bags. We would say they've held up&nbsp;
reasonably well after 8 years of use. But as to be&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:20.800
expected, they're a lot less plump compared to day&nbsp;
one. The covers are washable, but they can get a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:26.160
bit warm if you're lying down on the part with a&nbsp;
synthetic fabric. Overall, we've really enjoyed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:31.760
these. And even though we've had the opportunity&nbsp;
to try many different floor seats over the years,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:31.760 --> 00:02:36.720
bean bags still have a place in our home&nbsp;
as they're the most suitable for lounging.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:36.720 --> 00:02:42.000
They're not the most space efficient compared to&nbsp;
our other seating options, but we would definitely&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:48.240
miss them if they were gone. So, we would still&nbsp;
want to have at least one of these around. The&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:48.240 --> 00:02:54.320
next two items are simple, relatively inexpensive&nbsp;
shelves in the living room. There's really not&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:54.320 --> 00:02:59.360
much to say about these. If you like the way&nbsp;
they look and if you need some shelf space,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:59.360 --> 00:03:05.360
these would get the job done. But if we were to&nbsp;
do it over again today, we might consider having&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:12.400
one larger stationary shelf instead. Originally,&nbsp;
we had the idea that we could wheel the projector&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:18.400
into our bedroom if we wanted to, but we have&nbsp;
never done that once in the years we've been here.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:24.080
Our verdict, these were appropriate purchases&nbsp;
back then and have served their purpose well, but&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:31.440
we may consider making a change to these moving&nbsp;
forward. In the kitchen, we have our pegboard,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:31.440 --> 00:03:37.280
which is another one of our favorites in these&nbsp;
series. Pegboards are obviously very versatile&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:42.960
with their modular flexibility, and we have seen&nbsp;
them look good in a bunch of different settings,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:48.560
whether it's in the kitchen or in an office&nbsp;
setup. In our case, the biggest advantage of a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:48.560 --> 00:03:54.000
pegboard is that it doesn't protrude from the&nbsp;
wall that much, providing storage space along&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:54.000 --> 00:04:01.200
this narrow walkway, allowing us to conveniently&nbsp;
access frequently used cooking utensils. Also,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:07.760
this wood finish suits our kitchen really&nbsp;
well, so we would definitely buy these again.

00:04:09.360 --> 00:04:14.640
Moving on to our bedroom. When we were shopping&nbsp;
for a wardrobe, we either didn't like the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:14.640 --> 00:04:20.320
off-the-shelf options that were available or they&nbsp;
didn't fit into this little nook of our bedroom.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:25.600
So, we had to be a bit creative and I think&nbsp;
we found a good balance with this solution.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:32.480
A simple clothes rack and these modular plastic&nbsp;
boxes. We've had a lot of questions about an open&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:39.440
wardrobe and the problem of dust. Naturally, yes,&nbsp;
there will be dust. That's why we keep our most&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:39.440 --> 00:04:45.680
frequently worn clothes out and less frequently&nbsp;
worn clothes inside the plastic drawers. We&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:51.520
actually started with a shorter stack of boxes,&nbsp;
but then realized we could use a bit more space,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:51.520 --> 00:04:56.720
and that's when we got a couple more, which is&nbsp;
a good example of why we like having modular&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:56.720 --> 00:05:03.280
storage. The only minor complaint we have with&nbsp;
these lightweight boxes is balance. We can't&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:03.280 --> 00:05:08.560
just carelessly pull the drawers out too far or&nbsp;
the weight of the clothes will cause it to topple&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:08.560 --> 00:05:15.280
over. But it is what it is and we can't do much&nbsp;
about that. In the end, for this specific nook,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:20.560
we like what we have come up with, but we will&nbsp;
keep our options open if our wardrobe was in a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:28.080
different spot of the house. Our storage bed has&nbsp;
also been a solid purchase so far. As a bed frame,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:28.080 --> 00:05:33.600
it's sturdy and has a simple, understated&nbsp;
aesthetic. We like that it's relatively low&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:33.600 --> 00:05:39.760
profile compared to most other bed frames. And of&nbsp;
course, having additional storage has been really&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:39.760 --> 00:05:47.520
helpful. So no complaints, would buy again.&nbsp;
The next item are these storage cabinets in&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:47.520 --> 00:05:54.160
our office. You can see a recurring theme here.&nbsp;
These are also modular, and we might just need to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:54.160 --> 00:06:01.040
add a bit more storage soon. These cabinets work&nbsp;
and look okay, but honestly, these are clearly&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:01.040 --> 00:06:06.640
not designed to be high-quality furniture.&nbsp;
Things get misaligned here and there. So,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:06.640 --> 00:06:12.880
if you have a bit of OCD, this may not be the best&nbsp;
choice. If we were starting with a blank slate,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:12.880 --> 00:06:18.000
we might look around a bit more to see if there&nbsp;
are more solid options. But since we already have&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:24.480
these, we don't really mind expanding the storage&nbsp;
using the same system. It gets the job done.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:24.480 --> 00:06:30.000
And lastly, what used to be in this office&nbsp;
were our floor desks and chairs, which have&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:36.160
since been repurposed and reallocated to the&nbsp;
living room. Starting with the floor chairs,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:36.160 --> 00:06:41.440
these have a very solid folding mechanism that&nbsp;
still works great to this day. There were a lot&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:41.440 --> 00:06:47.360
of questions about toppling over when leaning&nbsp;
back, but the answer is no, you won't unless you&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:47.360 --> 00:06:54.720
are weirdly top-heavy. We have them in both small&nbsp;
and large sizes. And for some reason, the washable&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:54.720 --> 00:07:01.440
cover of the large one shrank after we washed it,&nbsp;
and now we can no longer zip it up. Generally,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:07:01.440 --> 00:07:07.920
both of us prefer the smaller one. Anyway, it's a&nbsp;
